\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 08, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104rhb1665702962182.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/rhb1665702962182.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/rhb1665702962182.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"rhb1665702962182\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Database Access on SEQ\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">\n</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"rhb1665702962182__section_w2750ab1b5b1_w2751ab1b5_w2752ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1170634e54\">\n                        \n Logon Path\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rhb1665702962182__p_d58172e1_d58173e1_d58174e1\">Paths (for example, in assignment files) should be specified only for files. Logon information is not required.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rhb1665702962182__p_d58175e1_d58176e1_d58177e1\">The default extension for sequential files is <span class=\"ph filepath\">.udf</span>. You can assign an entity by entering the following line in the [ENTITIES] section of your assignment file:</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rhb1665702962182__p_d58178e1_d58179e1_d58180e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Entity</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">.udf = $seq</code>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rhb1665702962182__p_d58181e1_d58182e1_d58183e1\">The following line informs Uniface where the sequential file can be found, and then correctly assigns the entity:</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rhb1665702962182__p_d58184e1_d58185e1_d58186e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Entity.Model</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">= $seq:</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Entity</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">.udf</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"rhb1665702962182__section_w2753ab1b5b3_w2754ab1b5_w2755ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1170634e97\">\n                        \n Open/Close Support\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rhb1665702962182__p_d58190e1_d58191e1_d58192e1\">The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">open</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">close</span> ProcScript commands are not supported. If they are issued, the SEQ connector does nothing.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"rhb1665702962182__section_w2756ab1b5b5_w2757ab1b5_w2758ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1170634e112\">\n                        \n Using SEQ for the Repository\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rhb1665702962182__p_d58196e1_d58197e1_d58198e1\">You can use the SEQ data connector for Uniface system information in a production environment, as long as you are aware of the limitations stated in <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"thj1665702664733.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/thj1665702664733.html\" title=\"When opening sequential files, Uniface attempts to establish both read and write access. If this fails, Uniface opens them with read-only access. Users can read data, but any attempt to update the data causes the appropriate warning or error message to be returned.\">Data Retrieval on SEQ</a>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"rhb1665702962182__section_w2759ab1b5b7_w2760ab1b5_w2761ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1170634e128\">\n                        \n Accessing Multiple Databases\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rhb1665702962182__p_d58202e1_d58203e1_d58204e1\">Not applicable. The sequential connector creates and accesses files, not tables.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"rhb1665702962182__section_w2762ab1b5b9_w2763ab1b5_w2764ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1170634e137\">\n                        \n I/O Channels\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rhb1665702962182__p_d58208e1_d58209e1_d58210e1\">One I/O channel is open for each open file.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531590\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531590\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Database Access on SEQ Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 08, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Database Access on SEQ Logon Path Paths (for example, in assignment files) should be specified only for files. Logon information is not required. The default extension for sequential files is .udf . You can assign an entity by entering the following line in the [ENTITIES] section of your assignment file: Entity .udf = $seq The following line informs Uniface where the sequential file can be found, and then correctly assigns the entity: Entity.Model = $seq: Entity .udf Open/Close Support The open and close ProcScript commands are not supported. If they are issued, the SEQ connector does nothing. Using SEQ for the Repository You can use the SEQ data connector for Uniface system information in a production environment, as long as you are aware of the limitations stated in Data Retrieval on SEQ . Accessing Multiple Databases Not applicable. The sequential connector creates and accesses files, not tables. I/O Channels One I/O channel is open for each open file. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}